On January 14, 2019, the President signed into law several bills, including the "Combating European Anti-Semitism Act of 2017," which aims to combat anti-Semitism both domestically and internationally. Other bills signed into law include the "Foundations for Evidence-Based Policymaking Act of 2018," which strengthens federal agency evaluation capacity and improves data sharing efforts; the "Water Infrastructure Improvement Act," which promotes the use of green infrastructure to reduce stormwater flows; and the "Nuclear Energy Innovation and Modernization Act," which supports the development and commercialization of advanced nuclear reactors. Additionally, the President signed bills that reauthorize and modify the Tropical Forest Conservation Act, provide training on preventing genocide and other atrocities to Foreign Service officers, and support access to education for displaced children, particularly girls.